## Document Formatting (apply to every report)

- **Font:** Times New Roman for all text (enforced via `.obsidian/snippets/lab-report-style.css` in the vault)
- **Figure captions:** always use plain Markdown italic — `*Figure N: text with $math$.*` — so that LaTeX renders correctly; the CSS snippet targets these automatically and applies dark teal (#006b73) and Times New Roman
- **Caption length:** 1 sentence max — key measurement or result only; no verbose re-explanation of the setup
- **Image embed syntax:**
  ```
  ![Fig N](assets/filename.png)

  *Figure N: Brief description with $math$ if needed.*
  ```
- **Table format:** standard Markdown tables; no double-pipe prefix
- **PDF export:** the snippet includes `@media print` A4 rules (page size, margins, color preservation, no figure/table/equation page-splits). Always keep each figure as an image-paragraph immediately followed by its `*Figure N: ...*` caption so they stay together on export.

