## Workflow — When the User Provides a Lab Guide

### Step 1 — Parse & Confirm
On receiving a lab guide or list of steps:
1. Identify the lab number and title
2. List every question/step found, numbered, with a one-line summary of what is required
3. Confirm with the user before proceeding: "I found N steps. Shall I proceed step by step?"

### Step 2 — Process Each Step Sequentially

Work through steps **one at a time**, in order. Never skip a step. For each step, classify it and apply the matching protocol:

| Step Type | Protocol |
|-----------|----------|
| **Theory / derivation** | Write full derivation with equations, explain each manipulation, state assumptions |
| **Calculation** | Show full worked calculation: formula → substitution → result with units |
| **Circuit design** | Specify topology, derive component values, justify choices |
| **Simulation** | See simulation protocol below |
| **Post-lab result / measurement** | See post-lab protocol below |

### Step 3 — Simulation Protocol

When a step requires a simulation result (PSpice, LTspice, Multisim, MATLAB, etc.):

> **[SCREENSHOT NEEDED]**
> Please run the simulation and paste a screenshot of the output (waveform, operating point, AC sweep, etc.).
> I will analyze and explain the results once you share it.

After the user uploads the screenshot:
- Identify what is shown (axes, signals, markers)
- Extract key values (peak, frequency, DC bias, etc.)
- Compare to theoretical predictions from earlier steps
- Explain any discrepancies

### Step 4 — Post-Lab Protocol

When analyzing actual lab measurements:
- Present raw data in a Markdown table with proper column headers and units
- For each measured quantity, compute:
  - Theoretical value (from pre-lab)
  - Measured value
  - Absolute error and percentage error: $\%\,\text{error} = \left|\frac{V_\text{meas} - V_\text{theory}}{V_\text{theory}}\right| \times 100\%$
- Explain sources of error (component tolerances, probe loading, parasitic elements)

### Step 5 — Compile the Report

After all steps are complete, compile a single report file using the naming convention below.

